documents.content:
Purpose,

,Overview of the Product & Engineering organization and members of the Consumer mega alliance. Complementing the limited views from workday and adaptive.

Context,

,The actual source of truth remains Workday for all employee data and reporting lines

,"In many cases managers have to have a way to plan ahead, to get an overview over a larger part of the org, to add more data like what programming languages someone can contribute in or a logical grouoping by triebs and squads. To avoid that everyone has to do the same work and to keep track of relevant metrics we maintain this central sheet for the whole alliance (Product, engineering)."

,The sheet is only shared with CS8+ managers. 

,For questions contact Holger Hammel

Main sheet - CMA,

,Please always use Filter views

,"CS8+ Tribe leads are responsible to keep the sheet up to date. This includes timely updates to status, dates of contract changes, reporting & squad assignments"

,TBD: how to sync and spot conflicts btw workday and adaptive and this sheet

,

(Dont change) Squad,

,"As indicated in the tab name, this view show the assignment of employees to squads."

,"The view is generated fromt the data in CMA, so please don't change any values"

(Copy to Overview)  Squads,

,Use this tab to COPY UNLINKED to other documents like Consumer Mega Alliance - Overview

Don't show in Squad view,

,"Set this checkbox to true if the person should not appear in the squad overview views. An example is if someone is on garden leave, then they would still appear in the list, but are not technically working in the squad anymore."

Values ...,

,Value Tabs are holding the values for dropdowns in CMA.

,"Adding or changing values impact those dropdowns and the validation, "

,"If a value has to change, e.g. a new squad or change of name, then change it here, and not on the dropdown fields in CMA"

Pivot,

,Various Pivot tables for analytics on the CMA data. 

,If you want to add new Pivots for a tribe etc please add a tab with preix Pivot:

Summary

blockers for OTP, which included events not being received in Katana and  

Salesforce, and an error during refund payments; participants confirmed  

that the first two issues, which manifested immediately in live internal  

orders, were R&D blockers for launch. Participants Alexander Matlin, Nikita  

Gorshkov, Edwin Torres, and Morteza Pourkazemi discussed that while  

functional testing was successful on staging, the Katana and Salesforce  

events needed live testing, and they theorized the lack of triggered events  

might be due to a business division issue requiring the grow go kit library  

or a configuration problem like "factor market" not being enabled, as the  

orchestrator "ops" likely emits these events. The team agreed that the  

refund payment issue, which Edwin Torres noted requires an update to the  

grow go kit library to properly handle the new business division, can be  

deferred to week two, while Alexander Matlin will contact Marat and Arem  

from the plans squad regarding the event production issues, escalating to  

an incident if no response is received by 12 PM Berlin time the following  

day, and Nikita Gorshkov asked Hamed Karimian to investigate a manual  

refund process in the interim.





Suggested next steps





Hamed Karimian will reach out to the customer care team to figure out a  

manual refund process for next week in case a refund is requested.



Edwin Torres will ping Nikita Gorshkov on the payment side channel where  

the ticket for the 'refund payments on OTP throws an error' is located.
